- cs.TY (Type Theory): The paper discusses the type system of the OCaml language and proposes a new formalization for polymorphic variants. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a new formalization for polymorphic variants that improves the predictability and expressiveness of the type system, which is relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper presents a formalization of polymorphic variants using set-theoretic types and subtyping, which is related to formal language theory.
